 {startupSession}‚ÜêStartupSession
‚çù This is a boot-strapping function run when APL starts.
‚çù It loads Link and uses that to load other Dyalog and/or user-specified things into  ‚éïSE and calls their Run functions.
‚çù Then it optionally uses Link to load a directory structure of text files into #.
‚çù Please do not rely on any other current behaviour of this function, as it may change without warning.
‚çù For more information about...
‚çù ‚àò Session Initialisation: https://help.dyalog.com/latest/#UserGuide/The%20APL%20Environment/Session%20Initialisation.htm
‚çù ‚àò Linking into #: https://help.dyalog.com/latest/#UserGuide/Installation%20and%20Configuration/Configuration%20Parameters/Load.htm
‚çù ‚àò Link: https://dyalog.github.io/link/latest

 :If ‚éïSE=‚éïTHIS
     '‚éïSE.Dyalog.Callbacks'‚éïNS‚äÉ‚éïSI
     startupSession‚Üê‚éïSE.Dyalog.Callbacks.StartupSession
     ‚éïSE.Dyalog.Callbacks.‚éïEX‚äÉ‚éïSI
     :Return
 :EndIf

 ‚éïSHADOW';'(‚âÝ‚äÜ‚ä¢)';‚éïIO;‚éïML' ‚çù sysvars
